node.text:
Did you know hippos have the ability to lock their jaws at nearly 180 degree angles?

Video by @cincinnatizoo 🦛

This feature, which makes a hippo look like it's yawning, is particularly important when hippos end up in conflict with other animals. The wide opening angle means that hippos can produce a bite force of 1,800 PSI—enough to break bones and snap wooden planks in two.

Interesting creatures down below! Which one would you least like to meet? (1-8) 😳
Video 1: @nautiluslive
Video 2: @onebreathdiver
Photo 3: © ennar0 / shutterstock
Video 4: @pelayosalinas
Video 5: @sheltondupreez
Video 6: @onebreathdiver
Video 7: via @underwater
Video 8: @david_palfrey
Please check out these talented photographers, their work is all fantastic!
